{#- â•â•â• INDUSTRY · Retail (BASELINE) · t-mofu→t-prose, dc-base chrome. Every
    baseline heading verbatim at level; content verbatim (no thin). ai-summary + faq
    rendered by t-prose from data (sec.aiH/faqH). #acctind-retail-definition speakable
    target preserved. â•â•â• -#}

{#- DEFINITION — speakable target id PRESERVED. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-definition">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In plain terms</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Retail accounting, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- CHALLENGES — 3 H3s verbatim (r-3 dc-card). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-retail-challenges" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why retail books break</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Three places retailers lose the numbers.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Almost every messy retail file fails in the same three areas. Knowing which one you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ c.signal | safe }}</span><h3>{{ c.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- SUBVERTICALS — 6 H3s verbatim (r-3 dc-card, non-linked h3). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-subverticals">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who we serve</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Retail in every shape.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Each retail sub-vertical has its own POS pattern, inventory mix, and margin profile. The engagement model &mdash; fixed-fee, written scope, named ProAdvisor, work in your own QuickBooks file &mdash; stays consistent.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in subverticals %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ s.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- WHAT WE HANDLE — 6 H3s verbatim (r-3 dc-card, h3 linked + cta link). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-retail-handle" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What TechBrot handles</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Retail accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Every engagement is scoped to your location count, channel mix, POS platform, and SKU complexity &mdash; delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.num | safe }}</span><h3><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.title | safe }}</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a></p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INTEGRATIONS — checks-list. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-integrations">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Tools we work alongside</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Connected to where your retail runs.</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      {%- for t in integrations %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:16px;">{{ integrationsNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- COMPARISON — vs-table → cmp. Highlighted column = Multi-location omnichannel. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-comparison">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">When retailers outgrow simple books</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Single-store retail vs. multi-location omnichannel retail.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">The structural differences that explain why expanding from one store to multiple &mdash; or adding ecommerce on top of a store &mdash; multiplies accounting complexity. Knowing which side you&rsquo;re on tells us how the engagement scopes.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">Single-store retail vs. multi-location omnichannel retail accounting compared</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">What the books need to handle</th><th scope="col">Single-store retail</th><th scope="col" class="us">Multi-location omnichannel</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for r in comparisonRows %}
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="What the books need to handle">{{ r.need | safe }}</th><td data-col="Single-store retail">{{ r.single | safe }}</td><td class="us" data-col="Multi-location omnichannel">{{ r.multi | safe }}</td></tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:16px;">{{ comparisonNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PROCESS — 4 H3s verbatim (process-grid). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-retail-process" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How engagements work</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">From cash drawer chaos to real retail economics.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Every retail engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; built so POS, inventory, shrinkage, and location-level margin are accurate before anyone tries to make assortment or location decisions from them.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">{{ s.num | safe }}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ADVISORY — prose. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-advisory">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Beyond the books</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Reconciled registers are the start. Knowing what to stock is the point.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;margin-top:24px;">
      <a class="btn btn-cta" href="/contact/?intent=accounting" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:48px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:11px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- EXPERT REVIEW — firm-level byline + trust-row + meta-reviewed. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-retail-review">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="byline">
      <span class="prose-byline__mark"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 64 64" fill="#FCFBF8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"/><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"/></svg></span>
      <div><p class="prose-byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p><p class="prose-byline__meta">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot actually handles retail engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for technical accuracy on POS reconciliation, inventory and shrinkage, gift-card deferred revenue, multi-location and omnichannel P&amp;L, and multi-jurisdiction sales tax. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. TechBrot delivers the books and coordinates with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-15</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-15</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-15 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- RELATED — 4 H3s verbatim (r-2 hub-card). cta field present → cta label + arrow. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-retail-related" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Related services &amp; industries.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ r.href }}"><h3>{{ r.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ r.cta | replace(" &rarr;", "") | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
